==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Augmentative
<hw>Aug*ment"a*tive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>augmentatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the quality or power of
augmenting; expressing augmentation.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Aug*ment"a*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Augmentative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Augmentative
<hw>Aug*ment"a*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A word
which expresses with augmented force the idea or the properties of the
term from which it is derived; <as>as, <ex>dullard</ex>, one very
dull</as>. Opposed to <ant>diminutive</ant>.</def>
<rj><au>Gibbs.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Augmenter</ent>⟦br⟧
